# Supabase Security

## Client Selection

| Client | File | Use |
|--------|------|-----|
| Browser | `lib/supabase/client.ts` | Client Components, Realtime |
| Server | `lib/supabase/server.ts` | Server Components, Server Actions |
| Admin | `lib/supabase/admin.ts` | Bypass RLS — server-only, never import in client code |

## RLS

- Enable RLS on every table with user data
- Policies check `auth.uid()` — never rely on client-side role checks alone
- Test policies: authenticated user can only access their own rows unless role permits

## Migrations

- One concern per migration file in `supabase/migrations/`
- Name format: `{timestamp}_{description}.sql`
- Always include RLS policies in the same migration that creates a table

## Anti-patterns

```ts
// ❌ Service role in a Client Component
import { adminClient } from '@/lib/supabase/admin'

// ❌ Skipping auth in a Server Action
await supabase.from('fights').insert(data)

// ✅ Server client + RLS enforces access
const supabase = await createClient()
await supabase.from('fights').insert({ ...data, user_id: user.id })
```
